<taxonomicName id="BEF5545195BA4A48E4585FD2D487A1F2" baseAuthorityName="Oberthuer" baseAuthorityYear="1923" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona jardanaria" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jardanaria">
<emphasis id="C52F1037C5DA643A98A2D39EC7EA2F6C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona jardanaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken id="DEDB81B0F7F8FB4A4DEFF28A854D38C0" originalValue="Oberthür">Oberthuer</normalizedToken>
), 
<taxonomicName id="73883D028042B0182952683D24B9D0F6" authorityName="Wilkinson" authorityYear="1968" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona media" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="media">
<emphasis id="338F2B2B6F6951BE3150E809700A6BEC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona media</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Wilkinson, 
<taxonomicName id="63EE540AA35FC168298E13994186CAD2" baseAuthorityName="Hampson" baseAuthorityYear="1893" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona innotata" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="innotata">
<emphasis id="DC36A6E97BB5C458F238848EE86180CB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona innotata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Hampson), 
<taxonomicName id="BF7C0C3894CD1431F2E6235DDDA4E592" baseAuthorityName="Leech" baseAuthorityYear="1898" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona sericea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sericea">
<emphasis id="2EDDB722736762D3714E9CC346BEAAE0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona sericea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Leech), 
<taxonomicName id="937DEB36EBE9FFF3FF4C82C864C7F96D" baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1867" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona quinaria" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quinaria">
<emphasis id="01F5829D9BFAF5B85215049C689A637C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona quinaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Moore), 
<taxonomicName id="EABD26AFE892B7F07B7B4CADEEA6A49B" baseAuthorityName="Hampson" baseAuthorityYear="1893" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona obliquilinea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obliquilinea">
<emphasis id="D9F82D256C5A9C4F7018EEF7CFD2AB05" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona obliquilinea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Hampson), 
<taxonomicName id="1E201E7E330B0A65CEA57E3DDAF68430" baseAuthorityName="Hampson" baseAuthorityYear="1893" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona idaeoides" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="idaeoides">
<emphasis id="41B71E6FFA8406912A5579230870A88D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona idaeoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Hampson), and 
<taxonomicName id="D63333D834DE44C3E32ED6CF9675E1F9" authorityName="Wilkinson" authorityYear="1968" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona spatulata" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spatulata">
<emphasis id="B3B10607E22F34284FB4C36E17671E70" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona spatulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Wilkinson. The former 10 species are recorded in China, and 
<taxonomicName id="3DBD7D718ABCBCECB05664AE08E45751" authority="Strand, 1917" authorityName="Guo &amp; Cheng &amp; Jiang &amp; Xue &amp; Han" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Guo &amp; Cheng &amp; Jiang &amp; Xue &amp; Han" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Auzatella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Auzatella pentesticha" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pentesticha">
<emphasis id="94641C37246538662C7816AC725B33EC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Auzatella pentesticha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Chu &amp; Wang is newly combined to 
<taxonomicName id="E551D8AB0F627F6B84EE3EDD2C0DE4FF" authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1888" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BD9B1FF5802E833F38AE96C2005E13BB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in this work.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="99621A6A2A1258F19052A897DE5F23D0" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">
Species of the 
<taxonomicName id="D7E2D7BEFF76A2AD9308EBE84BC7000F" baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1867" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona quinaria" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quinaria">
<emphasis id="1AC591C7C42A2F46E7A40230A3B3DFAC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona quinaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group share bipectinate or serrate antennae with some species of the 
<taxonomicName id="60520CE2B66EBF3E3CB0F5A86EF113AA" baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1867" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona triangularia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triangularia">
<emphasis id="D646ABB69939D4A31855FE9BCC94793E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona triangularia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="97C6962D461B6110A6E0725794ED9F3D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">mytylata</emphasis>
species groups. In the male genitalia, the uncus is usually single, but sometimes bifurcate or notched. The single uncus resembles that of species of the 
<taxonomicName id="41A72EC7A4A13433AAA66965C9F5BC0B" baseAuthorityName="Bryk" baseAuthorityYear="1943" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona derocina" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="derocina">
<emphasis id="0006327984720D01A1922A10697DF7F3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona derocina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group, but the group can be differentiated by the lack of sclerotization on the vinculum, and the large and broad saccus. The small and setose valva lacking a posterior projection also differs from those in the 
<taxonomicName id="3F4E6B96251A7809E913CEE1C7EC5D4A" baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1867" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona triangularia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triangularia">
<emphasis id="1677B03A1D39A56AEDB908F71769DDDE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona triangularia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="B9C6FD5A1FEF6AB7E936DEE140CA300E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">mytylata</emphasis>
species groups. The aedeagus is often characterized by the presence of a minute to large apical projection (not present in 
<taxonomicName id="640690FD89C8E63F0EFCF487D8A45882" family="Drepanidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. spilota" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" rank="species" species="spilota">
<emphasis id="800BDE345B215B8FDEDFD4E5688AE4D2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">D. spilota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="92A7F445E95A88EA3CEC33472BB76BA2" family="Drepanidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. obliquilinea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" rank="species" species="obliquilinea">
<emphasis id="3534A9DDF091F3F956F5A7F8D7411B3D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">D. obliquilinea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and the situation unknown in 
<taxonomicName id="3B72289853B8F45CA6169427CBFFB7C3" family="Drepanidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. innotata" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" rank="species" species="innotata">
<emphasis id="C032C930AEDA1DD38840111C2D824F83" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">D. innotata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="13BC8E21022863B68DBEDBB1224F5C45" family="Drepanidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. idaeoides" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" rank="species" species="idaeoides">
<emphasis id="3E59429D0C2A20774CA146DB70007818" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">D. idaeoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The eighth sternite is modified with short octavals, and the tergite is often shallowly to moderately concave, occasionally straight or protruding with tiny lateral projections. The female genitalia lack an ostial plate; the ductus bursae is short and broad, and the corpus bursae usually has an accessory sac and a long and thin signum.
</paragraph>
